# README

RIME: Rime Input Method Engine, an input method designed for the Chinese language family

Features:

- customizable input schemas powered by a generalized algorithm base
- major functionalities found in modern input method stereotypes
- introduction of avant-guarde (sometimes PQliar :) design
- open-source && tweakability++
- cross-platform; linux/ibus, windows, (yet to come...)

Sub-projects:

- ibus-rime : Linux/ibus client
- weasel    : Windows client
- squirrel  : planning Mac OS X client

Related works:

- combopy   : an innovative chord-typing practice
- brise     : rime schema repository
- essay     : vocabulary and language model
- plume     : web-based input method
- zhung-r10n: an romanization scheme for Zhungyuan Mandarin phonology

The rime alphabet: |
    zed wy ex,
    double-u vee u,
    tee ess ar,
    cue pee o,
    en em el kay jay i aitch,
    gee ef e dee cee bee a.

Epilogue: |

    Sorry for the temporary short of documentation. Feel free to explore.

    For lastest news, visit rime project home page:
    http://code.google.com/p/rimeime/

    Questions go to <rime-devel@googlegroups.com>

    Thanks.
